{"article_id":"M4vPkWpjiOk13eOq","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"So you think","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"you 've succeeded","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"in making it through the ObamaCare website maze ,","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"and now you have health insurance ?","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"You might want to think again .","depth":2},{"id":5,"text":"Despite the Obama administration 's claim","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"that HealthCare.gov is `` vastly improved , ''","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"insurance companies are still grappling with error-riddled files","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"fed to them from the flawed website .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"The lingering glitch could cause major problems weeks down the road ,","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"resulting in people thinking","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"they 've signed up","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"when insurance companies have no record","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"of them doing so .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"These so-called `` back-end '' problems were largely glossed over","depth":5},{"id":15,"text":"when federal health officials confidently claimed over the weekend","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"they had met their own goals","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"for improving the website","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"by Dec. 1 .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"Administration officials said early Sunday","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"that they have fixed roughly 400 computer `` bugs ''","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"and increased capacity","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"so the site can now handle more than 800,000 users daily with an error rate of less than 1 percent .","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"Jeff Zients , the official","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"appointed to fix the ObamaCare site since its disastrous Oct. 1 rollout ,","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"said","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"it is `` night and day from what it was . ''","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"But insurers continue to deal with the same set of problems","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"that have shaken their confidence for weeks in the system","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"they have to rely on","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"to enroll new customers .","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"`` Until the enrollment process is working from end-to-end ,","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"many consumers will not be able to enroll in coverage , ''","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"Karen Ignagni , president of America 's Health Insurance Plans , said in a statement .","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"She said","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"`` significant 'back-end ' issues ' '' need to be addressed , and particularly the `` ongoing problems ''","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"processing enrollment files","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"known as `` 834 files . ''","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"These are forms","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"that give insurance companies basic information about would-be customers .","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"But they 've had problems for weeks .","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"AHIP spokesman Robert Zirkelbach told FoxNews.com","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"that companies are receiving duplicative and inaccurate forms ,","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"and `` in some cases , plans are not getting the enrollment files at all . ''","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"The New York Times reports","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"that companies are getting flooded with phone calls from people","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"who think","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"they 've signed up","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"-- though they 're not on record as having done so .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"The ongoing problems mean that people","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"who believe","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"they have a health plan","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"could be in for a surprise on Jan. 1 .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"Though the administration has given people until the end of March","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"to sign up for coverage","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"if they want to avoid a fine ,","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"coverage for many is supposed to start on Jan. 1 .","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"That leaves just 30 days","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"to fix the remaining glitches .","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"`` This is not a functioning website yet , ''","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"James Capretta , senior fellow with the Ethics and Public Policy Center , told .","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"-- Bloomberg reports","depth":6},{"id":62,"text":"that after the troubled Oct. 1 launch , the Obama administration boosted its enrollment numbers for November","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"-- with roughly 100,000 people signing up through HealthCare.gov .","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"That figure , however , is far short of the original goal","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"of enrolling 800,000 people in the first two months .","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"-- ' own attempt","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"to log in at HealthCare.gov on Sunday","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"was spotty at best .","depth":6},{"id":69,"text":"After the site allowed the user to fill in personal information like a Social Security number ,","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"a notice came up","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"that said :","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"`` Verification system temporarily unavailable . ''","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"In addition , the site asked","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"if a navigator or insurance broker was helping with the application .","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"After `` none of these people '' was selected ,","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"a screen came back","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"that said , incorrectly :","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"`` You 've told us","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"another person is helping you complete the application . ''","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":159,"left":84,"right":158,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":84,"left":83,"right":4,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":83,"left":0,"right":82,"